admirable /ˈædmərəbəl/

1. ADJ An admirable quality or action is one that deserves to be praised and admired. 值得钦佩的 

例： She did an admirable job of holding the audience's attention. 她做了件值得钦佩的事：吸引了观众的注意力。 

2. admirably ADV 值得钦佩地 

例： Peter had dealt admirably with the sudden questions about Keith. 彼得对关于基思的突如其来的问题处理得值得人钦佩。

